race.comment: WEIRD GOODBYES (6) is a six-start maiden who finished fifth, beaten 6 lengths, when resuming from a spell last start over 1000m at Cloncurry. Strips fitter now and is capable of taking this out. MIDORI FOREST (2) is yet to break through after five starts but not far off a win. Placed two back then missed the frame but was thereabouts last time over 1200m at Birdsville. Should be poised just off the speed despite the draw. Key runner who can get off the mark. UP TO US (5) was one of the favoured runners last time but could only manage to finish seventh over 1200m at Richmond Qld. Suited in this line up and is among the better hopes. HELLUVAPUNCH (10) turned in another moderate effort last start when 8 lengths from the winner in seventh over 1000m at Cloncurry. Has his share of ability and is a top-three prospect from the favourable draw.
